response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Reverse Words\", \"description\": \"Write a function `reverse_words` that takes a string as input and returns a new string with the words in reverse order. \\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef reverse_words(s: str) -> str:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `s` (str): A string containing one or more words separated by spaces.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns a new string with the words from the input string in reverse order.\", \"code\": \"def reverse_words(s: str) -> str:\\n  return ' '.join(reversed(s.split()))\", \"tests\": [\"assert reverse_words(\\\"hello world\\\") == \\\"world hello\\\"\", \"assert reverse_words(\\\"python is fun\\\") == \\\"fun is python\\\"\", \"assert reverse_words(\\\"\\\") == \\\"\\\"\", \"assert reverse_words(\\\"one\\\") == \\\"one\\\"\"] }"
